<task id="031" project="spaarke-environment-provisioning-app">
  <metadata>
    <title>Refactor RegistrationDataverseService URL Resolution</title>
    <phase>4</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, refactor</tags>
    <estimate>1.5h</estimate>
    <status>pending</status>
    <dependencies>030</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    <goal>Refactor RegistrationDataverseService so it can operate against different Dataverse URLs per environment instead of being hardwired to the default environment URL at construction time.</goal>
    <context>Currently the service reads DefaultEnvironment's DataverseUrl at construction and uses it for all operations. After this refactor, methods that operate on per-environment data (like creating system users, adding team membership) should accept the target Dataverse URL or environment config.</context>
    <constraints>
      - The service's own operations (CRUD on sprk_registrationrequest) target the admin Dataverse (spaarkedev1)
      - Per-environment operations (create system user, add to team) target the environment's Dataverse URL
      - May need separate HttpClient or token per target URL
      - Keep thread safety with semaphore pattern
      - This is a significant refactor — be careful with existing functionality
    </constraints>
  </prompt>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Registration/RegistrationDataverseService.cs</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/dataverse/web-api-client.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-environment-provisioning-app/spec.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step>Read RegistrationDataverseService.cs fully</step>
    <step>Identify which methods target admin Dataverse vs per-environment Dataverse</step>
    <step>Design approach: separate base URLs, or accept URL parameter</step>
    <step>Implement URL resolution changes</step>
    <step>Update token management for multiple Dataverse URLs</step>
    <step>Build and verify</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Read</tool>
    <tool>Edit</tool>
    <tool>Bash</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Registration/RegistrationDataverseService.cs (modified)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Service can operate against different Dataverse URLs</criterion>
    <criterion>Admin operations still target spaarkedev1</criterion>
    <criterion>Per-environment operations use correct URL</criterion>
    <criterion>Thread safety maintained</criterion>
    <criterion>Build passes</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
